article.headline: Middle Tenn. St. 65, Denver 48
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. (AP) -- Tommy Gunn scored 17 points and had eight rebounds as Middle Tennessee defeated Denver 65-48 on Saturday night. Denver (13-10, 5-6 Sun Belt Conference) never led in the second half, but tied the game 37-37 on a dunk by Yemi Nicholson, who finished with 12 points. Middle Tennessee (13-10, 5-5) answered with a 7-0 run capped by Gunn's layup with 15:11 left. The Pioneers came back within a basket at 44-41 after two free throws by Brett Starkey with 12:35 remaining, but Kyle Young hit back-to-back jumpers for the Blue Raiders. Neither team shot the ball well from 3-point range. Middle Tennessee went 3-for-15, while Denver went 3-for-17. Middle Tennessee's Mike Dean scored 16 points and Michael Cuffee added 12. Rodney Billups scored 12 points for the Pioneers.
